      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Are collagen gummies better than collagen powder?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Collagen powder typically delivers a higher dose per serving at a lower cost per gram compared to gummies. A standard powder serving provides 10 to 20 grams of collagen, while gummies generally provide 2.5 to 5 grams. However, gummies offer superior convenience and compliance. Research shows that supplement adherence is the single greatest predictor of outcomes, and the pleasant taste and portability of gummies can significantly improve daily consistency. For individuals who will reliably take gummies every day but would skip an unflavored powder, the gummy format delivers better real-world results despite the lower per-serving dose.' },
