    <h2 id="why-collagen">Why Collagen Gummies Are the Fastest-Growing Beauty Supplement</h2>

    <p>Collagen is the most abundant protein in the human body, forming the structural scaffold of skin, hair, nails, tendons, ligaments, and bones. It provides the tensile strength that keeps skin firm and the elasticity that allows it to bounce back. Starting in your mid-twenties, endogenous collagen production declines steadily, and by age 40, most adults have lost 10-20% of their dermal collagen density — a deficit that manifests as fine lines, sagging skin, and slower wound healing.</p>

