    </div>

    <p>Oral collagen supplementation works by a different mechanism than topical application. Hydrolyzed collagen peptides — collagen that has been enzymatically broken down into fragments of 2,000-5,000 daltons — survive digestion and enter the bloodstream as bioactive dipeptides and tripeptides, primarily hydroxyproline-glycine and proline-hydroxyproline. These peptides signal fibroblasts in the dermis to increase new collagen, elastin, and hyaluronic acid production.</p>

