      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Type II Collagen</strong>
        <p>Found in cartilage. The key type for joint cushioning and mobility. Undenatured Type II (UC-II) at 40mg daily has shown joint benefits in clinical trials. Not the primary target for beauty supplements.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Type III Collagen</strong>
        <p>Co-exists with Type I in skin and blood vessels. Supports skin suppleness and cardiovascular elasticity. Often paired with Type I in beauty formulations for comprehensive dermal support.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Hydrolyzed Peptides</strong>
        <p>Collagen broken into 2,000-5,000 dalton fragments for intestinal absorption. The bioactive form that actually reaches the dermis. All effective collagen gummies use hydrolyzed peptides, not intact collagen protein.</p>
      </div>
